eir lives as their children begin the story anew, skewed through the kaleidoscope of historical events.Inspired by Jenny White's own experiences as a student in Turkey during this tumultuous period as well as original oral histories of Turks who lived through it, Turkish Kaleidoscope reveals how violent factionalism has its own emotional and cultural logic that defies ideological explanations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aPolitical violencezTurkeyzAnkaraxHistoryy20th centuryvFictionvComic books, strips, etc. 0aTurksxSocial conditionsvFictionvComic books, strips, etc. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / Turkey & Ottoman Empire.2bisacsh  aA Survivor’s Tale.  aAKP.  aAlan Moore.  aAnd Here My Troubles Began.  aArt Spiegelman.  aBerlin.  aChristopher Houston, Istanbul, City of the Fearless.  aCity of Light.  aCity of Smoke.  aCity of Stones.  aDare to Disappoint.  aGezi.  aJason Lutes.  aMarjane Satrapi.  aMaus II.  aMaus.  aOzge Samanci.  aPekesen.  aPersepolis.  aTurkey in Turmoil.  aanthropology.  aclass struggle.  acoup.  aculture.  agender.  aleftist.  amasculinity.  aoral history.  apolitical demonstration.  apolitical upheaval.  apolitics.  aradicalization.  arightist.  asocial change.  awomen.  ayouth protest.1 aGündüz, Ergün.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishz978311075408708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021z9783110753851oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z97831107